ClientSocket - Class in clueNetwork
Class semantics and roles:
The ClientSocket is the main utility for communicating over a socket connection.
ClientSocket() - Constructor for class clueNetwork.ClientSocket
Default Constructor
Takes 0 arguments, calls ClientSocket("127.0.0.1");
(Same as calling connect("127.0.0.1" , Utilities.defaultPort);)
ClientSocket(String) - Constructor for class clueNetwork.ClientSocket
Constructor 01
Takes 1 argument, calls ClientSocket(addr , Utilities.defaultPort);
(Same as calling connect(addr , Utilities.defaultPort);)
ClientSocket(String, int) - Constructor for class clueNetwork.ClientSocket
Constructor 02
Takes 2 arguments, calls ClientSocket(addr, port);
(Same as calling connect(addr,port);)
ClientSocket(Socket) - Constructor for class clueNetwork.ClientSocket
Constructor 03
Takes 1 arguments, calls connect(Socket sktIn);
(Same as calling connect(Socket sktIn);)

connect(String, int) - Method in class clueNetwork.ClientSocket

createPlayer(String, Socket) - Method in class clueServer.Users
Purpose: Create an additional player instance in the array

Precondition: There is an array of some number of players between 0 and 5
Postcondition: There is one more player added and the player has its thread started
Pseudo-Code:
BEGIN
-> put the number of connected users into "INDEX"
-> create a Player object in element INDEX + 1 of Player object array
-> start the newly created Player thread
END
createServerComponents() - Method in class clueServer.Server
Purpose: Once the server-side program has started executing, this method begins instantiating the necessary logic and user-management components components

Precondition: Server-side program has been launched
Postcondition: Server-side program has objects necessary to continue pre-game setup
Pseudo-Code :
BEGIN
- create an instance of a GameLogic object and point internal GameLogic reference to it
- create an instance of a Users object and reference internally
- - This will start the ServerListener listening as well, the listen() method is called from the ServerListener's constructor
END

LAST MODIFIED: Michael Philippone, 12 DEC 2008
